## 🚀 Step-by-Step Technical Guide: Battery-Efficient Continuous Geolocation Monitoring

---

### ✅ Step 1: Understand Android Geolocation APIs & Permissions

Ensure your app requests the required permissions at runtime:

```xml
<!-- AndroidManifest.xml -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION" />
```

> ⚠️ For continuous location, `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION` is mandatory. This permission must be granted at runtime (Android 6.0+).

Also ensure your app uses **LocationManager** or **Fused Location Provider** (FLP) via `LocationServices`.

---

### ✅ Step 2: Set Up a Foreground Service (Required for Background Location)

Foreground services allow apps to run background tasks without being killed by the OS, but they must be **visible to users** and provide a reason.

